==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Free coinage
<hw>Free coinage</hw>. <def>In the fullest sense, the conversion of
bullion (of any specified metal) into legal-tender coins for any person
who chooses to bring it to the mint; in a modified sense, such coinage
when done at a fixed charge proportionate to the cost of the
operation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Free-denizen</ent>⟦br⟧
